description:
&lt;p&gt;Based in Skipton House (London), the Provider Development directorate works with regional teams, local health systems and the provider sector to ensure that we have strong and successful providers, working collaboratively within strong and successful systems, in the best interests of local patients, populations and staff. Provider policy sits within this directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly team responsible for developing evidence-based advice and recommendations on high profile, important issues to support NHS England and NHS Improvement and the provider sector to make decisions that improve the delivery of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team looks beyond the headline questions to understand the real issues behind them, drawing on multiple sources of information on the provider sector and our knowledge of the policy and regulatory landscape. We use a range of structured tools to tackle each issue and engage widely to understand different perspectives and move thinking forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our current work programme covers a broad range of high profile and interesting areas, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;delivery of NHS long term plan commitments to support small rural acute providers and facilitate provider collaboration with systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;deep dive reviews into important issues facing providers in response to Covid-19 that fall at the interface between national policy and operational delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;policy development and advise on providing-facing issues, including the NHS oversight framework, legislation, independent provider regulation and policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the Senior Manager is to support, and lead as appropriate, the design and delivery of major policy and strategy projects, leading and delivering workstreams and managing stakeholders at all levels internally and externally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;owning the development of policy workstreams to support the development of the provider landscape and policy across NHS England and NHS Improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;delivering key strategic projects spanning the themes of oversight and improvement, the use of regulatory levers including competition and procurement, driving improvement in quality, integrated and new models of care and efficiency and productivity in the NHS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;developing policy and strategy for Provider Development and supporting decision makers within the organisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;working collaboratively with national health and care bodies, including the government, and the sector itself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder manages Analysts and discrete workstreams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to be an inclusive team that is flexible and supports a wide range of lived experience and obligations beyond work. We would encourage anyone that matches the person specification to make an application. However, we recognise that sometimes people have a question about working on our team that is not covered in the job description or person specification. If you would like an informal discussion about the role or how we are supporting inclusivity, please contact Steve Beales (steve.beales@nhs.net).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to speak to members of our team and find out more about how we work in practice, please register to attend a virtual open evening on Wednesday November 11, 5-6pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email NHSI.Policyteam@nhs.net to confirm your place and for any further details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Steve Beales&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: steve.beales@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
